cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with a computer vision task of liver segmentation from CT volumes using a deep learning approach. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a deep supervision mechanism during the learning process, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of a conditional random field model for refining segmentation results indicates that it may also belong to the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with medical imaging, which suggests that it may belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of a fully convolutional architecture and the mention of optimization difficulties suggest that it may also belong to the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
